label.value: transforming growth factor beta1-type II receptor complex

definition.value: A protein complex that consists of a dimeric transforming growth factor beta (TGF-beta) type II receptor bound to a TGF-beta1 dimer.

label.value: transforming growth factor beta1-type II receptor-type I receptor complex

definition.value: A protein complex that is formed by the association of a ligand-bound TGF-beta type II receptor dimer with a TGF-beta type I receptor dimer.

label.value: transforming growth factor beta receptor homodimeric complex

definition.value: A homodimeric receptor complex that consists of two TGF-beta receptor monomers.
A protein complex that is formed by the association of a heterodimeric interleukin-12 receptor complex with an interleukin-12 heterodimer.
A protein complex that contains the cell surface signaling molecule CD19, the Ras guanine nucleotide exchange factor Vav, and the regulatory subunit alpha of phosphatidylinositol 3-kinase (PI3K).
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with carbon monoxide (CO).
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with nitric oxide (NO).
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with and responding, e.g. by conformational change, to changes in the cellular level of carbon monoxide (CO).

label.value: regulation of transcription by carbon monoxide

definition.value: Any process involving carbon monoxide that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of transcription.
A protein complex that consists of an alphav-beta3 integrin complex bound to osteopontin.
A protein complex that consists of an alphav-beta1 integrin complex bound to osteopontin.
A protein complex that consists of an alphav-beta5 integrin complex bound to osteopontin.
A SNARE complex that contains synaptobrevin 2 (VAMP2), SNAP-25, syntaxin 1a, and complexin I (or orthologs thereof).
A SNARE complex that contains synaptobrevin 2 (VAMP2), SNAP-25, syntaxin 1a, and complexin II (or orthologs thereof).
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with the telomerase RNA template or to RNA complementary to it.
Catalysis of the reaction -  purine NTP + H2O -eq- purine NDP + phosphate, to drive the unwinding of a DNA or RNA helix.
Catalysis of the reaction -  GTP + H2O -eq- GDP + phosphate, to drive the unwinding of a DNA or RNA helix.
Catalysis of the transfer of a methyl group from S-adenosyl-L-methionine to a pseudouridine residue in an rRNA molecule.
Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + rRNA -eq- S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + rRNA containing N3-methylpseudouridine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + rRNA -eq- S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + rRNA containing 2'-O-methylguanosine.

Catalysis of the reaction -  2 S-adenosyl-L-methionine + adenine(2503) in 23S rRNA -eq- S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + 5'-deoxyadenosine + L-methionine + rRNA containing C2-methyladenine(2503) in 23S rRNA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + rRNA -eq- S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + rRNA containing C5-methyluridine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + rRNA -eq- S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + rRNA containing N3-methyluridine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + rRNA -eq- S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + rRNA containing N7-methylguanine.
A SNARE complex that contains synaptobrevin 2 (VAMP2), SNAP-25, and syntaxin 1a (or orthologs thereof).
A SNARE complex that contains synaptobrevin 2 (VAMP2), SNAP-25, and syntaxin 2 (or orthologs thereof).
A SNARE complex that contains synaptobrevin 2 (VAMP2), SNAP-25, and syntaxin 3 (or orthologs thereof).
A SNARE complex that contains synaptobrevin 2 (VAMP2), SNAP-25, and syntaxin 4 (or orthologs thereof).
A SNARE complex that contains endobrevin (VAMP8), SNAP-25, and syntaxin 1a (or orthologs thereof).
A SNARE complex that contains endobrevin (VAMP8), SNAP-25, and syntaxin 2 (or orthologs thereof).

Interacting selectively and non-covalently with fibrinogen, a highly soluble hexameric glycoprotein complex that is found in blood plasma and is converted to fibrin by thrombin in the coagulation cascade.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a type V collagen trimer.
Combining with thrombospondin and transmitting the signal to initiate a change in cell activity.
The region of the prospore membrane that extends to surround the spore nucleus -  coated with specific proteins that are thought to play a role in prospore membrane organization.

label.value: prospore membrane spindle pole body attachment site

definition.value: The region of the prospore membrane to which the spindle pole body (SPB) is anchored -  the prospore membrane extends from the SPB attachment site to surround the spore nucleus.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with the D- or L-enantiomer of fructose, the ketohexose arabino-hex-2-ulose.
A membrane-bounded vesicle that is released into the extracellular region by fusion of the limiting endosomal membrane of a multivesicular body with the plasma membrane.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with an RNA polymerase molecule or complex.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a proline-rich region, i.e. a region that contains a high proportion of proline residues, in a protein.
A SNARE complex that contains cellubrevin (VAMP3), VAMP4, and syntaxin 16 (or orthologs thereof).
A SNARE complex that contains cellubrevin (VAMP3), VAMP4, endobrevin (VAMP8), and syntaxin 6 (or orthologs thereof).
A SNARE complex that contains syntaxin 6, syntaxin 16, and Vti1a (or orthologs thereof).
A SNARE complex that contains VAMP4, syntaxin 6, syntaxin 16, and Vti1a (or orthologs thereof).
A protein complex in which at least one of the proteins is a cytochrome, i.e. a heme-containing protein involved in catalysis of redox reactions.

A secretory organelle that forms part of the apical complex -  a small, threadlike structure located is close proximity to the subpellicular microtubules. Its contents include a rhomboid protease (PfROM1 in Plasmodium falciparum) that moves from the lateral asymmetric localization to the merozoite apical pole and the posterior pole upon release of merozoites from schizonts.

Interacting selectively and non-covalently with the titin Z domain, which recognizes and binds to the C-terminal calmodulin-like domain of alpha-actinin-2 (Act-EF34), adopts a helical structure, and binds in a groove formed by the two planes between the helix pairs of Act-EF34.
A clathrin-sculpted lipid bilayer membrane-enclosed vesicle after clathrin release and containing monoamines.
The volume enclosed by the membrane of the clathrin-sculpted monoamine transport vesicle.
The lipid bilayer surrounding a clathrin-sculpted monoamine transport vesicle.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a chromo shadow domain, a protein domain that is distantly related, and found in association with, the chromo domain.
